ercial products, generating multi-million USD in revenue (Covasant).\n- Flagship Achievement: Built and globally institutionally BrewRIGHT platform, integrating 13 ERP systems to analyze multi-billion-dollar cash flows and surface regulatory, fraud, and antitrust risks with 85% accuracy (AB InBev).\n- Spend Analytics: Identified $80M+ in cost-saving and risk mitigation opportunities (AB InBev).\n- Zero-to-One Build: Formed a 100-member global data team, owning $2M budget for leading compliance analytics platforms across 50+ countries (AB InBev). Led SDLC/Agile teams in building products from scratch.\n- NPS Growth: Improved Net Promoter Scores for analytics services by 50+ points (AB InBev).\n- SMInsights: Created the self-service analytics marketplace, reducing BI dependency for a $1B client (Intel).\n- International Exposure: Managed and collaborated with teams across Israel, the USA, South Africa, China and Brazil.\n\n# CORE COMPETENCIES \n- Strategic: Engineering Leadership, Enterprise Software Architecture & Technology Strategy and Roadmapping, Product ideation to scaled delivery, Global Engineering Org Design & Scaling, Architecture Governance, Technical Standards, Program & Portfolio Delivery,  Zero-to-One Product Engineering, C-Suite & Board Engagement, Innovation, Risk & Compliance Strategy, Global Cross Function Collaboration, Commercial and P&L Ownership, Industry–Academia Partnerships\n- Technical Stack: AI/GenAI Systems, MLOps & LLMOps, Cloud-Native Architecture (Azure, AWS), Distributed Systems, Data Platforms & Analytics, DevOps & CI/CD, Security & Governance, Reliability Engineering, Python, Microservices\n- Stakeholders: C-suite, Compliance, Regulators, Legal, Risk, InfoSec, Product, Sales, Customer-Success, IT, Academia\n\n# AWARDS & RECOGNITION\n- BrewRIGHT: Recognized by HBS, Financial Times, American Lawyer, and New York Law Journal – AB InBev\n- Managerial Excellence Award – AB InBev\n- Shortlisted for Great Managers Award – AB InBev\n- Innovation Coin (2x) – Intel\n- Hall of Fame Award – IBM ITD GD\n- Special Recognition Award – Samsung\n\n# WORK EXPERIENCE\n## Vice President of Engineering and AI\nCovasant\n\nBengaluru, Karnataka, India\n\nApr 2023–Present\n\nSeries B SaaS startup delivering AI-driven products and services to Fortune 500 across 15 countries, supported by ~200 engineers and five global offices.\n- AI Strategy and Platform Leadership | Fortune 500 B2B SaaS customers| Reporting to CTO.\n- Defined and executed agentic AI roadmap, aligning platform capabilities with business use cases and accelerated productization. Established AI-led IP strategy, creating reusable frameworks, accelerators, and proprietary models for competitive advantage.\n- Guided cloud-native infrastructure build on public cloud, enabling always-on pipelines, model serving, and monitoring at transaction scale ($1.2T+)\n- Transitioned from internal capabilities to commercial SaaS monetization, supporting GTM and enterprise sales.\n- Led cross-functional teams aligning engineering roadmap with market priorities.\n- Launched AI-powered document fraud detection protecting five Fortune 500 clients.\n- Launched GenAI and agentic workflows (NLP chat, NL to SQL, multi agent orchestration) with governance frameworks.\n\n## Global Director, Advanced Analytics\nAB InBev\n\nBengaluru, Karnataka, India\n\nNov 2017–Mar 2023\n\nWorld’s largest brewer. 500+ brands, $50B+ revenue. Compliance analytics platforms: 20+ global regions.\n- Partnered with legal, audit, and compliance teams to influence regulatory posture and board confidence.\n- Digital Risk Assessment: Engineered an enterprise platform addressing cyber threats and SOX controls.\n- Engineered unified global data backbone integrating procurement, sales, and vendor data with governance.\n- Introduced data stewardship and governance best practices ensuring integrity, compliance, and AI-ready data.\n\n## Analytics Product Owner & Delivery Lead\nIntel\n\nBengaluru, Karnataka, India\